  "verdict": "INVALIDATED for runtime integration. The route-batched row-reduce Metal kernel is numerically close enough for a spike, and applying route weights before down is basically performance-neutral under gather_qmm (median 0.9949x vs standard). But the Metal hidden primitive is much slower than MLX gather_qmm (median 0.4708x), and the full route proxy is also much slower (median 0.5227x vs standard). Do not build this row-reduce route-batched kernel into Capstan. The next plausible path is a true optimized GPU kernel using tiled/simdgroup dot structure or a C++/MPS/Metal Performance Shaders path, not one threadgroup per route/output row."
